title: Nebraska Highway 105
text:
Nebraska Highway 105 is a highway in southeastern <a href="Nebraska">Nebraska</a>. Its southern terminus is at an intersection with <a href="Nebraska%20Highway%208">Nebraska Highway 8</a> south of <a href="Humboldt%2C%20Nebraska">Humboldt</a>. Its northern terminus is at an intersection with <a href="Nebraska%20Highway%2067">Nebraska Highway 67</a> west of <a href="Brock%2C%20Nebraska">Brock</a>.
Route description.
Nebraska Highway 105 begins at an intersection with <a href="Nebraska%20Highway%208">NE 8</a> south of <a href="Humboldt%2C%20Nebraska">Humboldt</a>. It heads in a northbound direction through farmland, turning slightly to the northeast before entering Humboldt. At the north edge of the city, the highway meets with <a href="Nebraska%20Highway%204">NE 4</a> and runs concurrently to the west for about . At that point, NE 105 splits and heads directly to the north. It passes by <a href="Nebraska%20Highway%2062">NE 62</a> east of <a href="Elk%20Creek%2C%20Nebraska">Elk Creek</a>. Further north, it intersects with <a href="U.S.%20Highway%20136">US 136</a> and runs concurrently northward for about a mile. NE 105 continues to the north near <a href="Johnson%2C%20Nebraska">Johnson</a>. To the north of Johnson, the highway meets its termination point at <a href="Nebraska%20Highway%2067">NE 67</a> west of <a href="Brock%2C%20Nebraska">Brock</a>.
